      "name": null,
      "patch_url": null
    },
    "body": "`CTransaction` currently has `public` data members that are marked `const`. Details why this is problematic, what the alternatives are, and how to fix it are given [here](https://purplekarrot.net/blog/bitcoin-tidy-transaction.html) or [here](https://njump.me/nevent1qqsw9tv4k2twul6u83pq5zamz8y6waaglxrwgxzu7f7t4s6p99ctcuqpz3mhxue69uhhyetvv9ujuerpd46hxtnfdupzqrcxrljwdpfz2qn5a57hse6ez6pkd34pe0wpeskmktt2p62yeket3klllm).\r\n\r\nThe code is refactored using the following steps:\r\n\r\n1. Public observer functions are added to `CTransaction` for each data member.\r\n2. A `bitcoin-tidy` check is added to rewrite direct data member access to use an observer function.\r\n3. A \"scripted-diff\" that is the result of running the `bitcoin-tidy` check with `-fix`.\r\n4. Making `CTransaction`'s data members private.\r\n\r\nThe result is that `CTransaction` has regular semantics for copy, move, and assignment. The refactoring is a prerequisite for further refactoring that will untangle the type from serialization logic (read about those plans [here](https://purplekarrot.net/blog/serialization.html) or [here](https://njump.me/nevent1qqsx8r92d75zdmsdcmtqqhulrvhdjzxx2elfp8ws0k0lpnwjfxg0yjqpp4mhxue69uhkummn9ekx7mqpz3mhxue69uhhyetvv9ujuerpd46hxtnfdupzqrcxrljwdpfz2qn5a57hse6ez6pkd34pe0wpeskmktt2p62yeketqvzqqqr4guphdnrw)) which will result in better reasoning and faster compilation.",
